[1] Florida
Date: Mon 29 Apr 2019 4:55 PM EDT
Source: CBS Miami/NSF [edited]
https://miami.cbslocal.com/2019/04/29/florida-hepatitis-a-outbreak-continues-to-grow-2


An outbreak of hepatitis A is growing concern among Floridians. The outbreak continues to grow across the state, with 70 cases reported last week [week of 22 Apr 2019], according to the Florida Department of Health website. As of Sat 27 Apr 2019, 954 cases of the contagious liver disease had been reported in the state in 2019, compared to 549 cases in all of 2018 and 276 cases in 2017.

Health officials say the outbreak began in 2018, and 97 percent of the cases since 1 Jan 2018, have likely been acquired in Florida. During that period, Pinellas county has had the most cases, with 319. Pinellas has been followed by Pasco county with 267 cases; Orange county with 179 cases; and Hillsborough county with 165 cases, according to the Department of Health website.

